gametext: Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Opponent may not 'react' to or from here. Power -1 when opponent has a starfighter present with higher maneuver.
lore: Created by General Dodonna and Rebel engineer Walex Blissex. Designed to combat the speed and maneuverability of the TIE interceptor. Jamming suite disrupts enemy communications.
name: A-wing

gametext: Deploy on your A-Wing. May target a starfighter or squadron for free. Draw destiny. Add your starship's maneuver. Target hit if total destiny > twice target's defense value.
lore: Equipped with targeting sensor system. Weapon mounts pivot up to 60 degrees to improve targeting.
name: A-wing Cannon

gametext: Deploys -2 to \ul Home One\ul0. Adds 3 to power of any capital starship he pilots. Your capital starships deploy -1 to same system. Once per game, may take one Mon Calamari character or Admiral's Order into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Mon Calamari \b leader\b0  of Rebel fleet. Master military strategist. Early prisoner of Grand Moff Tarkin. Convinced his people to join the Alliance.
name: Admiral Ackbar

gametext: If Luke is about to be lost from table and Vader is present, shuffle Reserve Deck and draw destiny. Add 6 if Emperor present. If total destiny > 12, Vader crosses to Light Side, Luke is not lost, opponent loses 6 Force, and Emperor (if present) is lost (Immune to Sense.)
lore: "You were right about me. Tell your sister . . . you were right."
name: Anakin Skywalker

gametext: If you control with a starfighter, opponent's \ul Dreadnaught\ul0-class cruisers are deploy +3 and your Force generation here is +3.
light_side_text: If you control with a starfighter, opponent's \ul Dreadnaught\ul0-class cruisers are deploy +3 and your Force generation here is +3.
name: Aquaris

gametext: * Replaces 3 B-wings at one location (B-wings go to Used Pile). Permanent pilots provide total ability of 3. Each of its weapon destiny draws is +1.
lore: Utilizes dense formations on attack missions to concentrate firepower. This tactic is particulary effective in defeating deflector shields.
name: B-wing Attack Squadron

gametext: May add 1 pilot (suspends permanent pilot). Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. May fire two or more weapons during battle. Each of its ion cannon weapon destiny draws is +3.
lore: Carries weapon systems capable of taking on escort frigates and capital starships. Armed with high-powered ion cannon used to disable deflector shields.
name: B-wing Bomber

gametext: May add 1 pilot. May fire two or more weapons during battle. Each of its weapon destiny draws is +2. Immune to attrition < 4 when Ten Numb piloting.
lore: Blue Squadron B-wing. Ordered to lead attack on \ul Executor\ul0. Drew enemy fighters away from strike force led by General Calrissian and Commander Antilles.
name: Blue Squadron 5

gametext: Deploy -2 to Roche. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2 and adds 1 to power. May fire two or more weapons during battle. Each of its weapon destiny draws is +2.
lore: B-wings ordered to attack Imperial command starships at Battle of Endor. Armed with armor-penetrating missiles. Maintained by Verpine mechanics.
name: Blue Squadron B-wing

gametext: Each pilot deploys -1 (or -2 if an admiral) aboard a capital starship. Each capital starship with a pilot character aboard is immune to attrition < 4 (or adds 2 to immunity if starship already has immunity). During each of your control phases, opponent loses 1 Force for each battleground site your general controls that is related to a system you occupy.
name: Capital Support

gametext: Allows your starship weapons at same location to fire and deploy for 1 less Force. While aboard your capital starship, adds 1 to each of its weapon destiny draws (2 when targeting a capital starship).
lore: Mon Calamari computer technician. Expert in power systems. His skills are desperately needed by Rebel fleet. \b Gunner\b0.
name: Captain Verrack

gametext: Deploy on table. While your Z-95 occupies a system or cloud sector, once per turn your scout at a related exterior site may add one battle destiny (if Z-95 is Tala 1 or Tala 2, may also add one destiny to total power only).
lore: Attack plans for General Madine's commandos often require coordinated air support. A number of Z-95 headhunters have been modified to operate in this role.
name: Close Air Support

gametext: Deploys -2 aboard Tala 1. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Tala 1, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. When opponent deploys a spy or scout to same (or related) exterior site, opponent loses 1 Force.
lore: Alliance \b spy\b0  and \b scout\b0. Often flies support missions for General Madine's commandos.
name: Colonel Cracken

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When he is piloting a Y-wing, once per battle you may cancel and redraw your battle destiny just drawn. While he occupies the Renegade system, Imperial Control is flipped and Imperial Occupation may not be flipped.
lore: \b Leader\b0  of Gray Squadron. Prefers to fly venerable Koensayr starfighters instead of newer models because "they've always gotten me home in one piece."
name: Colonel Salm

gametext: At each system where any player does not have both a starfighter and a capital starship present, that player's starships there are power -2. At sites related to systems you occupy, during each battle opponent may draw no more than one battle destiny. Once during each of your deploy phases, you may deploy one combat vehicle from your Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
name: Combined Fleet Action

gametext: Each starfighter that fires a weapon in battle is power +3 for remainder of battle. Once per turn, you may cancel and redraw your starship weapon destiny just drawn. At sites related to systems you occupy, your characters who have immunity to attrition each add 2 to immunity and 1 to each of that character's weapon destiny draws.
name: Concentrate All Fire

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your bomber, A-wing, freighter or transport. May target a starship for free. Draw destiny. Add 1 if targeting a starfighter or squadron. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Used by veteran smugglers. Defend transports from maneuverable TIE fighters. Frequently used to arm Rebellion transports and freighters.
name: Concussion Missiles

gametext: Reduces X by 3 on Docking And Repair Facilities when a Star Cruiser is held there. When he is at a docking bay where you have just deployed a starfighter, once per turn you may retrieve 1 Force.
lore: Corellian dock mechanic. Defected to the Alliance with General Madine. Manages staff of 75 starfighter and 12 star cruiser mechanics in \ul Home One's\ul0  rear quadrant.
name: Corporal Marmor

gametext: Adds 1 to each of his character weapon destiny draws (2 when firing a rifle and all your ability here is provided by scouts). While on Endor, adds 1 to your Force drains at your exterior Endor sites where you have a scout of ability > 2 (and no Ewoks).
lore: Self-taught marksman and \b scout\b0  from a rural region of Chandrila. Inspired by Mon Mothma to join the Alliance. Newly recruited into Madine's commandos as a field technician.
name: Corporal Midge

gametext: If you have a leader at your war room, peek at top card of opponent's Reserve Deck. You may place it on bottom of that Reserve Deck.
lore: \b Hologram\b0  technology allows efficient communication of complex intelligence during war room briefings.
name: Critical Error Revealed

gametext: May add 5 pilots, 6 passengers, 3 starfighters and 1 vehicle. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Each of its weapon destiny draws is +2. Capital starships it 'hits' are power -5.
lore: Fleet rear guard. Weapon batteries hard-wired to central targeting processor. Coordinates vicious crossfire against enemy capital starships.
name: Defiance

gametext: Deploy on your X-wing, Y-wing or B-wing. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Add 1 if targeting a capital starship. Otherwise, subtract 1. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Often modified by Rebel technicians. Heavy warhead provides increased armor penetration. Decreased maneuverability and effectiveness against starfighters.
name: Enhanced Proton Torpedoes

gametext: Deploys -2 to \ul Home One\ul0. Adds 3 to power of any capital starship she pilots. When piloting a Star Cruiser with another Mon Calamari pilot aboard, unless opponent has total ability > 6 piloting here, reset opponent's total battle destiny here to 0.
lore: Mon Calamari deck officer. Brilliant tactical analyst. One of several brave \b leaders\b0  of Mon Calamari refugees from Imperial invasion of her planet.
name: First Officer Thaneespi

gametext: Deploys -2 aboard \ul Falcon\ul0. Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a freighter, adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. When he attempts to "blow away" Death Star II, adds 2 to total.
lore: \b Leader\b0. \b Gambler\b0. Fair pilot. Lando was given the rank of General for "a little maneuver" at the Battle of Taanab. Willing to lead Rebel starfighters in a crazy attack.
name: General Calrissian

gametext: Deploys -2 aboard your Star Cruiser or to same location as your Admiral. Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. Adds 1 to power and forfeit of each of your A-wings at same and related locations.
lore: Engineer who worked with Jan Dodonna to design the A-wing starfighter. Given honorary rank due to his service to the Rebellion.
name: General Walex Blissex

gametext: Deploy -2 to Endor. May add 2 pilots and 2 passengers. Immune to Tallon Roll. Immune to attrition < 4 when Lando or Nien Nunb piloting (< 6 when both).
lore: The \ul Millennium Falcon\ul0  relies on heavily upgraded speed and maneuverability to survive in combat. General Calrissian's starship at Battle of Endor.
name: Gold Squadron 1

gametext: May add 2 pilots or passengers. Ion cannons may fire free aboard. Each of its ion cannon weapon  destiny draws is +2. Immune to attrition < 4 when Salm or Kian piloting.
lore: Y-wing flown by Colonel Salm at the battle of Endor. Ordered to disable capital starships between General Calrissian and the Death star.
name: Gray Squadron 1

gametext: May add 2 pilots or passengers. Immune to attrition < 3 when Lieutenant Telsij or Karie Neth piloting (when both, immune to attrition < 5 and adds one destiny to power only).
lore: Flown by Lieutenant Telsij as Colonel Salm's wingman. Part of Gray Squadron during the Battle of Endor.
name: Gray Squadron 2

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a Y-wing, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. When a starship he pilots fires an ion cannon, once per turn, may draw two weapon destiny and choose one.
lore: Veteran pilots of the reliable Koensayr starfighter were assigned by Ackbar to a key role at Endor. Both the pilots and their venerable Y-wings were up to the task.
name: Gray Squadron Y-wing Pilot

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Green Squadron 1, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Adds 3 to total weapon destiny of any starfighter he pilots firing at a starfighter with lower maneuver.
lore: \b Leader\b0. Assigned to fly fighter screen for General Calrissian at Endor.
name: Green Leader

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Power -1 when opponent has a starfighter present with higher maneuver. Immune to attrition < 4 when Green Leader piloting.
lore: Constructed at Chardaan Shipyards, a zero-gravity facility. Typically used as an escort for Y-wings or B-wings on critical attack missions.
name: Green Squadron 1

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Power -1 when opponent has a starfighter present with higher maneuver. Maneuver +2 at a Death Star II sector. Immune to attrition < 4 when Tycho Celchu piloting.
lore: Flown by Tycho Celchu at the Battle of Endor. Modified canopy improves pilot vision in tight confines. Assigned to fly top cover for \ul Millennium Falcon\ul0.
name: Green Squadron 3

gametext: Deploy -2 to Sullust or same system or sector as Green Leader. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2 and adds 2 to power. Power -1 when opponent has a starfighter present with higher maneuver.
lore: A-wing starfighters from Green Squadron. Assigned mission of screening Rebel capital starships from enemy fighters and bombers.
name: Green Squadron A-wing

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting an A-wing, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise and is forfeit +2.
lore: Many top X-wing pilots transferred to A-wing squadrons when the new starfighter entered service. The best A-wing pilots were selected to fly for Green Squadron at the Battle of Endor.
name: Green Squadron Pilot

gametext: If your piloted unique (*) starfighter is present with opponent's piloted starfighter during your move phase at a non-cloud sector, relocate both to related system. OR Target your starfighter in battle. During this battle, your other starships may not be targeted by weapons.
lore: "And see if you can get a few of those TIE fighters to follow you."
name: Head Back To The Surface

gametext: USED: Add 1 to your battle destiny just drawn. STARTING: Deploy up to three Effects if each of them deploys for free, is always immune to Alter and has "deploy on table" (or "deploy on your side of table") in its game text. Place Interrupt in Lost Pile.
lore: At the Battle of Endor, Rebel starships fought to defend key capital starships, such as the \ul Redemption\ul0.
name: Heading For The Medical Frigate

gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on your Star Cruiser (or Star Destroyer). Adds 2 to power. May target a starship using 2 Force. Draw two destiny. Subtract 1 when targeting a capital starship. Otherwise, subtract 6. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Built to penetrate the armor of the toughest Star Destroyers. Cooling technology pilfered from the Empire.
name: Heavy Turbolaser Battery

gametext: May add unlimited pilots, passengers, vehicles and starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilots provide total ability of 4. Immune to attrition < 8 (< 10 when Ackbar piloting).
lore: Command ship of the Rebel fleet. 1200 meters long. Masterpiece of aesthetic form. Most heavily armed and armored ship in the fleet. Admiral Ackbar's personal flagship.
name: Home One

dark_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here requires 7 Force. Your transit to here requires +9 Force.
gametext: Your docking bay transit from here is free. If you occupy, opponent may not move to this site.   Your docking bay transit from here requires 7 Force. Your transit to here requires +9 Force.
light_side_text: Your docking bay transit from here is free. If you occupy, opponent may not move to this site.
name: Home One: Docking Bay

dark_side_text: Force drain -1 here. When you initiate a battle here, add one battle destiny.
gametext: While you control with a Rebel here, \ul Home One\ul0  is deploy -5 and power +3.   Force drain -1 here. When you initiate a battle here, add one battle destiny.
light_side_text: While you control with a Rebel here, \ul Home One\ul0  is deploy -5 and power +3.
name: Home One: War Room

gametext: Deploy on table. Unless opponent occupies three battlegrounds, each time you must lose Force (except from your card, battle damage or a Force drain at a battleground), reduce the loss by 2. (Immune to Alter while you occupy any battleground).
lore: The final act of Luke's ascension to Jedi Knighthood was sending off his father, draped in the garb of Vader.
name: Honor Of The Jedi

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on table. Each time you win a battle or duel, opponent loses 1 Force (cannot be reduced) and stacks lost card here face down. When attempting to cross Vader over, add 3 to total destiny for each card in stack. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "I know there is good in you. The Emperor hasn't driven it from you fully."
name: I Feel The Conflict

gametext: Unique (*) starfighters without permanent pilots are immune to attrition < 4 (or add 2 to immunity if starfighter already has immunity). Starships without pilot characters aboard are power -2. At docking bays related to systems you occupy, your Force drains are +1. Once per turn, your starfighter just lost from a system may be relocated to a related docking bay.
name: I'll Take The Leader

gametext: Deploy on Luke if That's One and Count Me In are on table. When Han, Chewie, Leia and Luke are involved in the same battle, you may double your total battle destiny and Han, Chewie, Leia, and Luke are immune to attrition. Don't Get Cocky is a Used Interrupt.
lore: Luke completes the legendary foursome.
name: I'm With You Too

gametext: May add 5 pilots, 6 passengers, 1 vehicle and 3 starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Immune to attrition < 3 (< 4 if Rebel leader aboard).
lore: Communications starship. Often hosts first assignment for top prospects from among newly commissioned officers.
name: Independence

gametext: If your scout is in battle at an exterior planet site, subtract 3 from opponent's total battle destiny. OR Target opponent's character aboard an open vehicle moving to your scout's site. Draw destiny. If destiny +2 > ability, target goes to Used Pile.
lore: The Rebellion employs every advantage it has over Imperial machines. A corps of well-trained scouts can elude detection in proper terrain.
name: Insertion Planning

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything she pilots. While aboard your starship, adds 1 to each of its weapon destiny draws (2 if Gray Squadron 2 or when with Telsij).
lore: Gray Squadron 2's \b gunner\b0  at the Battle of Endor. Member of Rogue Squadron. Replaced Bothan pilot lost during secret mission ordered by Rebel command staff.
name: Karie Neth

gametext: Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots. When at a system, sector, or docking bay, once during each of your deploy phases, may subtract 2 from deploy cost of your unique (*) X-wing deploying here.
lore: Rescued from an Imperial detention center by Wedge Antilles. Rogue Squadron veteran. Assigned to Red Squadron at the Battle of Endor. Coordinates with Rebellion procurement.
name: Keir Santage

gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. While aboard your starship, adds 2 to each of its weapon destiny draws. While aboard a unique (*) Gray Squadron Y-wing at a system or sector, adds 1 to each of your Force drains there.
lore: Rogue Squadron pilot. Assigned as \b gunner\b0  aboard Colonel Salm's Y-wing at Battle of Endor, as part of Gray Squadron. Former member of Aggressor Squadron.
name: Kin Kian

gametext: Deploy on any system. Once per game, may take one \ul Home One\ul0  into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Your Force drains are +1 at battleground systems where you have a Star Cruiser piloted by a character. Effect canceled when Rendezvous Point on table. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: By recruiting the Mon Calamari, a race of master shipwrights, the Rebel starfleet gained capital starships rivaling the dreaded Imperial Star Destroyers.
name: Launching The Assault

gametext: Deploy on table. While you occupy a Renegade planet location, operatives are forfeit = 0, operatives do not add to Force drains and your Force drains may not be reduced. At any time, you may place Effect out of play to retrieve 1 Force. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The heroes of the Rebellion know that where there is life, there is hope.
name: Let's Keep A Little Optimism Here

gametext: May add 5 pilots, 6 passengers, 1 vehicle, and 3 starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. May go to Used Pile instead of Lost Pile when forfeited (unless 'hit').
lore: Winged star cruiser. Military transport for technical units. Afforded special care by the Alliance's top engineers.
name: Liberty

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Tala 2, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. While he occupies any Coruscant location, Empire's Sinister Agents is flipped and ISB Operations may not be flipped.
lore: Wingman of Colonel Cracken. \b Spy\b0  and \b scout\b0. Former agent of the Imperial Security Bureau. Defected and joined Rebel Intelligence. Seasoned combat veteran.
name: Lieutenant Blount

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When at a system, sector or docking bay, once during each of your deploy phases, may subtract 2 from deploy cost of your unique (*) Y-wing deploying here.
lore: One of only four attackers who survived the raid on the Imperial Academy at Carida. Gray Squadron pilot.
name: Lieutenant Telsij

gametext: When in battle at a site with Lando or Marmor, adds one destiny to total power only. When he is at a docking bay, once during each of your deploy phases, you may deploy one starship weapon from Reserve Deck on your starfighter present; reshuffle.
lore: Dock mechanic. Installs starfighter cannons. \b Gambler\b0. Followed Lando from Cloud City. Turned down assignment in rear guard to work on General Calrissian's starship.
name: Lieutenant s'Too Vees

gametext: Deploys -3 to \ul Home One\ul0  or Endor. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Power +2 when armed with a lightsaber. Subtracts 3 from any attempt to cross him over (even if captured). Immune to attrition < 5 (< 6 if alone or armed with a lightsaber, < 7 if both).
lore: \b Scout\b0  trained in the ways of the Force. Key figure for both the Alliance and the Empire. Desired by Vader as an ally, by Palpatine as a servant and by the Alliance as its savior.
name: Luke Skywalker, Jedi Knight

gametext: Deploy on Luke. Adds 1 to defense value and training destiny. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character, creature, speeder bike, or swoop for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Weapon of a truly powerful warrior. Constructed by Luke as part of his Jedi training.
name: Luke's Lightsaber

gametext: Deploys and moves like a starfighter. May add 1 pilot and 6 passengers. Has ship-docking capability.  Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. May use Covert Landing like a shuttle or starfighter (even while landed).
lore: Medium transport with boosted hyperdrive. Armor and capacity diminished. Crew trained for reconnaissance and swift intergalactic transport.
name: Luminous

gametext: Deploys -2 to any Star Cruiser. Adds 2 to the power of any capital starship he pilots. When piloting a Star Cruiser, adds 1 to hyperspeed and armor and cancels Lateral Damage targeting a starship at same system.
lore: Mon Calamari master engineer. Joined the Alliance to fulfill his personal goal of piloting star cruisers.
name: Major Haash'n

gametext: Power and forfeit +1 while present with Major Panno. When with Major Panno at a site, adds one battle destiny. When present with a Scomp link, cancels Counter Assault at a related site where you have a spy or scout.
lore: Communications expert. Staff monitors entire spectrum of electromagnetic signals. Politically minded. Followed Panno to the Alliance.
name: Major Olander Brit

gametext: While at a system or an exterior battleground site, allows you to activate up to 2 additional Force for each related exterior battleground site you occupy with a scout (limit 4 additional Force).
lore: Male Dresselian \b scout\b0. Former commando. Tactician. Works with General Madine to plan logistics of strike operations.
name: Major Panno

gametext: Deploys -4 to same system as any non-unique Star Cruiser. May add 3 pilots, 4 passengers and 1 vehicle. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Cannot be 'hit' by missiles.
lore: Frequently escorts Mon Calamari star cruisers. Personally assigned by Ackbar to main Rebel fleet. Advanced scanners continuously disrupt target acquistion signals.
name: Masanya

gametext: Deploy on table. While you control any three Coruscant, Death Star and/or Death Star II locations, or any one battleground site and one battleground system, all opponents Force drain bonuses everywhere are canceled. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: As the \ul Executor\ul0  crashed into the Death Star, hope surged throughout the ranks of the outmanned Rebel fleet.
name: Menace Fades

dark_side_text: If you control without a Star Destroyer, Force drain -1 here.
gametext: If you occupy with a Star Cruiser, opponent's Star Destroyers may not deploy here. Your Star Cruisers deploy -1 here.   If you control without a Star Destroyer, Force drain -1 here.
light_side_text: If you occupy with a Star Cruiser, opponent's Star Destroyers may not deploy here. Your Star Cruisers deploy -1 here.
name: Mon Calamari

gametext: Deploys only at Mon Calamari or any Rebel Base. May add 5 pilots, 6 passengers, 1 vehicle and 3 starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2.
lore: Mon Cal MC80 cruiser. Originally a civilian ship. Converted to military use following the liberation of Mon Calamari from the Empire.
name: Mon Calamari Star Cruiser

gametext: May add 4 pilots, 4 passengers, and 2 starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Turbolaser batteries and laser cannons may deploy aboard for free.
lore: Product of Imperial Kuat Drive Yards. Several captured by Alliance. Imperial crews promptly defected. Can be outfitted for a variety of missions requiring mid-size capital starships.
name: Nebulon-B Frigate

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When he is at a mobile sector, once per turn you may peek at top card of your Reserve Deck; you may place that card on top of Used Pile. When with General Calrissian, adds one battle destiny.
lore: Brilliant navigator. Former SoroSuub employee. Turned to pirating when that corporation backed the Empire. Tall for a Sullustan.
name: Nien Nunb

gametext: Deploy at the same system as your bomber. 'Explodes' if an opponent's starship deploys or moves here. Draw destiny. Add 2 when targeting a capital starship. Starship lost if total destiny > defense value. Orbital mine is also lost.
lore: Often stolen from the Empire. Used by the Rebellion to protect key spaceports. Can be released to cover the retreat of a fleeing strike force.
name: Orbital Mine

gametext: USED: If your Rebel of ability > 2 just won a battle or duel, randomly take into hand one card stacked on Insignificant Rebellion. (Immune to Sense.) LOST: If Luke is in battle (except with Vader), subtract 2 from each of opponent's battle destiny draws.
lore: "The Emperor knew, as I did, if Anakin were to have any offspring, they would be a threat to him."
name: Our Only Hope

gametext: Each of your admirals and generals is forfeit +1 for remainder of turn. OR If your admiral is in battle at a system (or your general, except Obi-Wan, is in battle at a site), you may either add one battle destiny or prevent opponent from drawing more than one battle destiny.
lore: In times of greatest need, the Rebellion relies on the brilliant leadership provided by commanders fighting for freedom.
name: Rebel Leadership

gametext: May add 1 pilot. [Death Star II] Wedge deploys -2 aboard (for free if deploying to Endor). When Wedge piloting, immune to attrition < 5 and adds 6 to total when targeted by Tallon Roll.
lore: Flown by Wedge Antilles as Red 2 at the Battle of Yavin. Redesignated at Endor. Rugged Incom fighter. Victory markers show its role in the attack on the first Death Star.
name: Red Squadron 1

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Hobbie deploys -2 aboard. When firing X-wing Laser Cannons, may use 2 Force to make X = 3. When Hobbie piloting, maneuver +2 and immune to attrition < 4.
lore: Flown by Derek 'Hobbie' Klivian during the attack on the second Death Star. Second-highest mission total of any X-wing in service for the Alliance.
name: Red Squadron 4

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Keir Santage deploys -2 aboard. Your other Red Squadron starfighters at same location are maneuver +1.
lore: Incom starfighter flown by Keir Santage. Flew twelve sorties against Imperial shipyards at Fondor.
name: Red Squadron 7

gametext: Deploy on table. During your deploy phase, you may reveal one unpiloted starfighter from hand to take its matching pilot character from Reserve Deck (or vice versa) and deploy both simultaneously; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Rebel starfighter squadrons take great pride in their proficiency and dedication. Alliance pilots train relentlessly until man and machine function as one.
name: Squadron Assignments

gametext: Deploy on table. Your Force generation is +1 at each docking bay you occupy (or +2 if you control). Your non-unique Star Cruisers are deploy -1 and may deploy to same battleground system as any Rebel starship. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The Alliance carefully chooses docking bays from which to launch limited offensives.
name: Staging Areas

gametext: Deploy on table. Twice per game, you may take one Mon Mothma or any general (except Obi-Wan) into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent's Force generation at Endor system is canceled unless Endor Operations on table. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "General Solo, is your strike team assembled?"
name: Strike Planning

gametext: Deploy on table. While you control a battleground site, your Force drain may not be modified or canceled by opponent at a system where you have a Star Cruiser or unique (*) starfighter, except by a 'react.' Place Effect in Used Pile if you lose a battle at a system.
lore: Admiral Ackbar's hit-and-fade tactics force the Imperial Navy to spread throughout the galaxy in a futile attempt to engage the Rebels.
name: Strikeforce

gametext: To move your starship between here and Death Star II, system it orbits or Mon Calmari requires -1 force.   Your starships deploy +1 here.
light_side_text: To move your starship between here and Death Star II, system it orbits or Mon Calmari requires -1 force.
name: Sullust

gametext: Deploy on table. Each turn, each of your characters, vehicles and starships may forfeit one of its weapons (except a lightsaber) using forfeit value = 3. Also, your forfeited weapons go to Used Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Veteran Rebel engineers know that weapon systems positioned for adequate coverage are vulnerable themselves.
name: Superficial Damage

gametext: Each player, if that player has a capital starship armed with a starship weapon in a battle, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise and, once per battle, may reduce the defense value of one opponent's capital starship present by 4 for remainder of the battle. At sites related to systems you occupy, your non-pilot warriors are deploy -1, defense value +2, and forfeit +1.
name: Taking Them With Us

gametext: May add 1 pilot. May be carried like a vehicle. Power and maneuver +2 at opponent's system (except battlegrounds) or at any sector. Immune to attrition < 4 when Colonel Cracken piloting.
lore: Heavily modified Headhunter. Operationally assigned to support Madine's commando team. Hyperdrive added to allow it to operate independently of capital starship support.
name: Tala 1

gametext: May add 1 pilot. May be carried like a vehicle. When your spy aboard, opponent's spies and scouts are deploy +2 to related sites. Immune to attrition < 4 when Lieutenant Blount piloting.
lore: Equipped with sophisticated sensor suite to monitor Imperial activity during Rebel commando operations. Hyperdrive allows long-range reconnaissance.
name: Tala 2

gametext: Deploys -2 aboard Blue Squadron 5. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Adds 2 to total weapon destiny of any B-wing he pilots.
lore: Sullustan \b gunner\b0. Pilot of Blue 5. Ordered to head a B-wing attack against Imperial command ships at the Battle Of Endor.
name: Ten Numb

gametext: If you just initiated a second battle this turn, deploy on table. When you lose a battle, you may place Immediate Effect in Used Pile to cancel all battle damage against you, unless Draw Their Fire on table. (Immune to Control.)
lore: "With the Imperial Fleet spread throughout the galaxy in a vain effort to engage us, it is relatively unprotected."
name: The Time For Our Attack Has Come

gametext: Deploy on table. If Yoda is on Dagobah and Jedi Test #3 is present with target apprentice, it is completed. Also, you may not play Surprise Assault. Each apprentice on Dagobah is landspeed = 2 and may not be targeted by Set For Stun. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "When nine hundred years old you reach, look as good you will not. Hmmm?"
name: The Way Of Things

gametext: [Front Side]: \ul Deploy Chief Chirpa's Hut (with [Death Star II] Luke and Luke's Lightsaber there), Endor: Landing Platform and I Feel The Conflict.\ul0 \par \b For\b0  remainder of game, you may not play Alter, Strangle, or Captive Fury. \par \b While\b0  this side up, your Force generation is +2 at Luke's site. While an Imperial is at Landing Platform, you may not Force drain or generate Force at Luke's location. When any Imperial is at Luke's site, Luke is captured (seized by an Imperial, if possible, even if not a warrior). \par \b Flip\b0  this card if Luke captured.\\par[Back Side]: \b While\b0  this side up, at end of each of opponent's turns, opponent loses 2 Force unless Vader is escorting Luke. At any time, an Imperial escorting Luke may transfer Luke to Vader, if present. Vader may not transfer Luke. Once during each of your turns, if Vader present with Luke (even as a non-frozen captive), may shuffle Reserve Deck and draw destiny. If destiny > 14, Vader crosses to Light Side, totally depleting opponent's Life Force. \par \b Flip\b0  if Luke neither present with Vader nor a captive.
name: There Is Good In Him/I Can Save Him

gametext: Deploy on table. Once per turn, may take The Force Is Strong With This One or [Death Star II] Anakin Skywalker into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. May use 2 Force to cancel You Are Beaten (unless canceling Uncontrollable Fury) or Dark Jedi Presence. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: When a Jedi dies, the spirit spreads through the Force and touches the living.
name: Twilight Is Upon Me

gametext: Deploys -2 aboard Green Squadron 3. Adds 3 to power of any starfighter he pilots. When piloting Green Squadron 3 or any X-wing, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
lore: \b Spy\b0  fighting for the memory of his homeworld of Alderaan. Rogue Squadron pilot. Volunteered to fly an A-wing at the Battle of Endor. Former TIE fighter pilot.
name: Tycho Celchu

characteristics: \b commander\b0, \b leader\b0, \b Corellian\b0, Rogue Squadron pilot
gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise (if Red 2 also adds 2 to maneuver.) When in battle with another Red or Rogue squadron pilot, once per battle may cancel one battle destiny just drawn.
lore: Corellian commander and \b leader\b0  of Rogue Squadron. Chose to have Rogue Squadron reclaim the designation "Red Squadron" at the battle of Endor.
name: Wedge Antilles, Red Squadron Leader

gametext: *\b Deploy\b0  on table. *\b Target\b0  a Skywalker who has completed Jedi Test # 5. While target on Dagobah, "move phase" on Save You It Can may be treated as "deploy phase". Until Jedi Test completed, battles you initiate at Vader's site are canceled and opponent loses 2 Force at start of your turn unless Vader is at a battleground site. *\b Attempt\b0  during your move phase when Vader with target (even as a non-frozen captive). Vader and target duel: Each player draws destiny. Add ability. Highest total wins. If target wins, test completed: *\b Leave\b0  on table. Add one battle destiny in every battle. Also, target is immune to attrition < 5.
name: You Must Confront Vader

gametext: Deploy on table. Opponent's Dark Jedi are defense value -1. Scanning Crew and 3,720 To 1 are canceled. You may place Effect in Lost Pile to take one [Endor] or [Death Star II] Effect that deploys for free into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Luke knew that while the dark side was quicker and more seductive, eventually evil would turn on itself.
name: Your Insight Serves You Well

gametext: May deploy -3 as a 'react.' May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1.
lore: Patrol ship. Modified for optimal crisis response time. Veteran crew experienced at monitoring shipping lanes and Imperial port traffic.
name: Accuser

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a Star Destroyer at a battleground system, adds 1 to your Force drains here and at each other battleground system controlled by a Star Destroyer within 2 parsecs of Chiraneau.
lore: Deep space transmissions expert. Piett's personal advisor. TIE ace promoted upon Piett's request.
name: Admiral Chiraneau

gametext: Deploys -2 to \ul Executor\ul0. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if a Star Destroyer). Your capital starships deploy -1 to same system. Once per game, you may take one Admiral's Order or any commander into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Veteran of the Imperial military machine. \b Leader\b0  of the Imperial fleet at Endor. Skilled at political maneuvering and appeasing his powerful superiors.
name: Admiral Piett

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Saber 1, adds one battle destiny and 2 to maneuver. Adds 1 to your total battle destiny for each of your piloted TIE Interceptors in same battle.
lore: Corellian Baron. \b Leader\b0  of famed 181st Imperial Fighter Wing. Taught at the Imperial Academy on Prefsbelt IV. Instructed Biggs Darklighter.
name: Baron Soontir Fel

gametext: At each system where any player does not have both a starfighter and a capital starship present, that player's starships there are power -2. At sites related to systems you occupy, during each battle opponent may draw no more than one battle destiny. Once during each of your deploy phases, you may deploy one combat vehicle from your Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
name: Battle Deployment

gametext: Deploy -1 to any mobile system. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. When with Vader in battle, may draw destiny and subtract that amount from opponent's total power.
lore: Stationed aboard command ship \ul Executor\ul0. Pilot known as 'Wampa' for icy precision in battle. Often serves as escort to Lord Vader's shuttle.
name: Black 11

gametext: [Front Side]: \ul Deploy Throne Room, Insignificant Rebellion and Your Destiny.\ul0 \par \b For\b0  remainder of game, Scanning Crew may not be played. Opponent's cards that place a character out of play may not target Luke. You may deploy Emperor (deploy -2) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent may deploy Luke from Reserve Deck (deploy -2; reshuffle) or Lost Pile. If Luke is present with Vader and Vader is not escorting a captive, Luke is captured and seized by Vader. Vader may not transfer Luke. \par \b Flip\b0  this card if Luke captured.\\par[Back Side]: \b While\b0  this side up, lose 1 Force at end of each of your turns. Once during each of your turns, when Vader, Luke (even as a non-frozen captive) and Emperor are all present at your Throne Room, you may initiate a Luke/Vader duel: Each player draws two destiny. Add ability. Highest total wins. If Vader wins, opponent loses 3 Force. If Luke wins, shuffle Reserve Deck and draw destiny; if destiny > 12, Luke crosses to Dark Side, totally depleting opponent's Life Force. \par \b Flip\b0  if Luke neither present with Vader nor a captive.
name: Bring Him Before Me/Take Your Father's Place

gametext: Adds 3 to power of any capital starship he pilots. While aboard a Star Destroyer, adds 1 to armor, adds 1 to hyperspeed and, once during each of your move phases, may cancel Landing Claw at same system or sector.
lore: Elite fleet engineer. Technically brilliant. Key operator of magnetic signature sensors monitoring Star Destroyer hulls.
name: Captain Godherdt

gametext: Deploys -2 aboard Scimitar 2. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When forfeited from a TIE/SA, also satisfies all remaining attrition and battle damage against you.
lore: Often flies as top cover during bombing runs. Served with Death Squadron. Narrowly escaped death by space slug. Scored several kills against Rebel blockade runners.
name: Captain Jonus

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While he controls opponent's non-battleground location, opponent generates no Force here. While he occupies opponent's Subjugated system, Liberation is flipped and Local Uprising may not be flipped.
lore: Piett's nephew. Once granted audience with Emperor. On fast-track to promotion. Absolutely fearless \b spy\b0.
name: Captain Sarkli

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if a starfighter). When piloting a TIE Defender and with Jendon, adds one battle destiny.
lore: Former member of Imperial Demonstration Team. Flew test flights during development of various TIE prototypes. Jendon's wingman. Has scored 24 combat victories.
name: Captain Yorr

gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Immune to attrition < 4 (< 5 while an Imperial leader aboard, < 6 while Thrawn aboard).
lore: Early model \ul Imperial\ul0-class Star Destroyer. Acting command ship in the absence of \ul Executor\ul0.
name: Chimaera

gametext: While at an exterior planet site, power +2, immune to attrition < 3 and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. When present with a Scomp Link, cancels Surprise Assault at a related site where you have a spy or scout.
lore: \b Scout\b0. Special forces \b leader\b0. Convinced superiors that wilderness survival and recon training are necessary for military dominance, despite technological superiority.
name: Colonel Davod Jon

gametext: Adds 3 to power and 1 to maneuver of anything he pilots. When piloting Onyx 1, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
lore: Senior test pilot ordered to shake down first TIE defenders assigned to fleet operations. Occasionally given honor duty of flying Vader's shuttle.
name: Colonel Jendon

gametext: Deploy on table. During your deploy phase, you may reveal one unpiloted starfighter from hand to take its matching pilot character from Reserve Deck (or vice versa) and deploy both simultaneously; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Being stationed at Endor during the construction of the second Death Star allowed Imperial pilots time to train in the latest starfighter combat techniques.
name: Combat Response

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When he is present with a Scomp link, once during each of your deploy phases, you may deploy one battleground system from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Elite Imperial \b scout\b0  and \b spy\b0. Often poses as a freighter captain making runs to the Outer Rim. Monitors activities of Rebels and other criminals.
name: Commander Merrejk

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your bomber, TIE Defender, freighter or transport. May target a starship for free. Draw destiny. Add 1 when targeting a starfighter or squadron. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Originally developed by smugglers and pirates as defense against starfighters. Adapted by the Empire to serve as onboard defense for slow moving bombers.
name: Concussion Missiles

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Saber 3, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Opponent may not 'react' to same system or sector.
lore: Flies Saber 3 in fighting 181st. Studied under Baron Fel at the Prefsbelt Imperial Academy; now flies as his wing. Nicknamed "Fel's Wrath." Watches the Baron's back.
name: DS-181-3

gametext: Adds 3 to power of any TIE he pilots. Once during each of your deploy phases, you may take one unique (*) TIE Interceptor into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Wingman of Major Phennir. Earned promotion to Fel's squadron by scoring 12 kills at Mon Calamari. Repeatedly refused further promotion so that he could remain in the 181st.
name: DS-181-4

gametext: Deploy on Vader. May target a character or creature. Draw two destiny. Target hit if total destiny > defense value. Also, during a duel, Vader may 'throw' this lightsaber to add 1 to each of his duel destiny draws (place lightsaber in Used Pile at end of duel).
lore: Vader's lightsaber. Symbol of the most feared man in the galaxy. Vader's control of the dark side of the Force allows him to wield this weapon in surprising ways.
name: Darth Vader's Lightsaber

dark_side_text: X = parsec of current position. Must deploy orbiting Endor. Death Star II locations are immune to Revolution. Opponent's Force drains +3 here unless That Thing's Operational on table.
gametext: X = parsec of current position. Must deploy orbiting Endor. Death Star II locations are immune to Revolution. Opponent's Force drains +3 here unless That Thing's Operational on table.
name: Death Star II

dark_side_text: Deploys only if Coolant Shaft on table. While That Thing's Operational on table, you may add one battle destiny during battles at Death Star II system and system it orbits.
gametext: When your starship moves from here, draw movement destiny. Add maneuver (if any). If total destiny < 2, starship is lost.   Deploys only if Coolant Shaft on table. While That Thing's Operational on table, you may add one battle destiny during battles at Death Star II system and system it orbits.
light_side_text: When your starship moves from here, draw movement destiny. Add maneuver (if any). If total destiny < 2, starship is lost.
name: Death Star II: Capacitors

dark_side_text: Deploys only if Death Star II system on table. Your TIEs at Death Star II locations may not Tallon Roll. Your non-Objective cards with 'Occupation' in title are canceled.
gametext: When your starship moves from here, draw movement destiny. Add maneuver (if any). If total destiny < 1, starship is lost.   Deploys only if Death Star II system on table. Your TIEs at Death Star II locations may not Tallon Roll. Your non-Objective cards with 'Occupation' in title are canceled.
light_side_text: When your starship moves from here, draw movement destiny. Add maneuver (if any). If total destiny < 1, starship is lost.
name: Death Star II: Coolant Shaft

dark_side_text: Your TIEs deploy -1 here. Your docking bay transit from here is free.
gametext: Your docking bay transit to or from here requires 8 Force (ignore other docking bay's text).   Your TIEs deploy -1 here. Your docking bay transit from here is free.
light_side_text: Your docking bay transit to or from here requires 8 Force (ignore other docking bay's text).
name: Death Star II: Docking Bay

dark_side_text: Deploys only if Capacitors on table. You may deploy That Thing's Operational from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Ominous Rumors is suspended.
gametext: When attempting to "blow away" Death Star II, add 1 to total destiny for each of your piloted starfighters here.   Deploys only if Capacitors on table. You may deploy That Thing's Operational from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Ominous Rumors is suspended.
light_side_text: When attempting to "blow away" Death Star II, add 1 to total destiny for each of your piloted starfighters here.
name: Death Star II: Reactor Core

dark_side_text: Once per game, you may take Emperor's Power into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
gametext: Immune to Revolution.   Once per game, you may take Emperor's Power into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
name: Death Star II: Throne Room

gametext: Deploy on Death Star II system. When opponent moves from a related sector, for each TIE armed with a weapon there, movement destiny is -3 (limit -9). Also, you may deploy either Combat Response or Imperial Arrest Order from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The Empire relied on the skill of its pilot corps to defend the Death Star reactor core from attack.
name: Desperate Counter

gametext: May add 4 pilots, 6 passengers, 1 vehicle and 2 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Laser Cannon Battery may deploy aboard (and may fire twice per battle).
lore: \ul Victory\ul0-class hull overhauled with powerful thrusters and latest hyperdrive technology. Engineered to support task forces combating Rebel starfighters.
name: Dominator

gametext: Never deploys or moves (even aboard a starship or vehicle) to a site opponent occupies. Where present, subtracts 3 from attempts to cross Vader over. Once per turn, you may take Force Lightning into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition.
lore: Sith Master and \b leader\b0  of Galatic Empire. Dark side mentor to Darth Vader. Controls the Empire by instilling fear in its subjects and greed in its governors.
name: Emperor Palpatine

gametext: May add 1 pilot and 4 passengers. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Emperor deploys for free aboard. While Emperor aboard, immune to attrition and adds one battle destiny.
lore: Transport used extensively by Emperor Palpatine. Extremely well guarded. Pilots ordered to maintain constant contact with all nearby Imperial strike forces.
name: Emperor's Personal Shuttle

gametext: Deploy on your Throne Room. You may not Force drain here. While Emperor here, opponent's characters are deploy +2 to Death Star II sites and, once per turn, you may lose Effect (or 1 Force from top of Reserve Deck) to add one battle destiny anywhere. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: From his throne room aboard the second Death Star, Emperor Palpatine monitors activity throughout the galaxy.
name: Emperor's Power

gametext: Deploy on Bunker. Imperials deploy -1 here. While Death Star II system orbits Endor and you control Bunker, at Death Star II system and each Death Star II site opponent may not deploy and must use +3 Force to move there. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Planetary scale shield projected from surface of Endor moon. Protected second Death Star during construction. Only another superlaser could penetrate it while operational.
name: Endor Shield

gametext: Each starfighter that fires a weapon in battle is power +3 for remainder of battle. Once per turn, you may cancel and redraw your starship weapon destiny just drawn. At sites related to systems you occupy, your characters who have immunity to attrition each add 2 to immunity and 1 to each of that character's weapon destiny draws.
name: Fighter Cover

gametext: Unique (*) starfighters without permanent pilots are immune to attrition < 4 (or add 2 to immunity if starfighter already has immunity). Starships without pilot characters aboard are power -2. At docking bays related to systems you occupy, your Force drains are +1. Once per turn, your starfighter just lost from a system may be relocated to a related docking bay.
name: Fighters Coming In

gametext: May add unlimited pilots, passengers and starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 3. Immune to attrition if target of Flagship Operations.
lore: Command ship of the Imperial Fleet at the Battle of Endor. Originally constructed at the Fondor ship yards. Admiral Piett stationed aboard.
name: Flagship Executor

gametext: Deploy on a Star Destroyer if five \ul Executor\ul0  sites on table. Your TIEs are deploy -1, forfeit +2, and destiny +2. At systems where you have a TIE, your Imperial capital starships are deploy -3 and your battle destiny draws are +1 each. (If on \ul Executor\ul0, immune to Alter.)
lore: "There's too many of them!"
name: Flagship Operations

gametext: Target any character (even a captive) present with Emperor. USED: Target is defense value -4 for remainder of turn. LOST: Emperor loses immunity to attrition and is defense value -2 for remainder of turn. Draw destiny. Target lost if destiny +1 > defense value.
lore: The Emperor is strong in the dark arts of the Force. He can direct pure energy to shoot forth from his outstretched fingers.
name: Force Lightning

gametext: Deploy on your Royal Guard (or use 3 Force to deploy on your other warrior). Adds 1 to defense value. May target a character or creature using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. If hit by a Royal Guard, target's power = 0.
lore: Uses microscopic vibrations emitted from its tip. Cuts through stone, metal and bone. Ceremonial weapon for most; deadly implement in the hands of an Emperor's Royal Guard.
name: Force Pike

dark_side_text: While you occupy, once per battle you may choose a target just 'hit' by a blaster or rifle (except [Permanent Weapon] weapons) to be lost.
gametext: Immune to Revolution.   While you occupy, once per battle you may choose a target just 'hit' by a blaster or rifle (except [Permanent Weapon] weapons) to be lost.
name: Gall

gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer (adds 2 to power) or any mobile system. May target a starship using 2 Force. Draw two destiny. Subtract 1 when targeting a capital starship. Otherwise, subtract 6. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: The ultimate in armor penetration. Relies on dense capacitor banks for massive firing charge. Capacitors regularly malfunction. Hitting maneuverable targets nearly impossible.
name: Heavy Turbolaser Battery

gametext: Take one admiral or general into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR If your admiral is in battle at a system (or your general is in battle at a site), you may either add one battle destiny or prevent opponent from drawing more than one battle destiny.
lore: The Emperor's high command is subjected to close scrutiny by the Imperial bureaucracy. Despite this apparent lack of trust, many turned out to be fine commanders.
name: Imperial Command

gametext: Deploy on table. Each turn, each of your characters, vehicles, and starships may forfeit one of its weapons (except a lightsaber) using forfeit value = 3. Also, your forfeited weapons go to Used Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: With its superior numbers, the Empire knowingly sacrifices the safety of many units and weapons in order to preserve the greater war machine.
name: Inconsequential Losses

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on table. Each time you win a battle, opponent loses 1 Force (cannot be reduced) and stacks lost card here face down. When attempting to cross Luke over (except with Epic Duel), add 3 to total destiny for each card in stack. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "Your fleet is lost. And your friends on the Endor moon will not survive. There is no escape, my young apprentice."
name: Insignificant Rebellion

gametext: Each player, if that player has a capital starship armed with a starship weapon in a battle, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise and, once per battle, may reduce the defense value of one opponent's capital starship present by 4 for remainder of the battle. At sites related to systems you occupy, your non-pilot warriors are deploy -1, defense value +2, and forfeit +1.
name: Intensify The Forward Batteries

gametext: Deploys -3 to Emperor's site. When with Emperor at a battleground site, adds 1 to your Force drains here. Once per turn, you may use 1 Force to place a card from hand on bottom of Used Pile and draw top card of Reserve Deck. Immune to attrition < 3.
lore: Imperial council member. Very cruel at heart. Has lusted for power his entire life. Predictable and controllable.
name: Janus Greejatus

gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Each of its weapon destiny draws is +2. Starfighters it 'hits' are power = 0.
lore: Incorporates latest design modifications from Kuat Drive Yards. Targeting computers outfitted with antenna locking, in-line calibration and helical-motion extrapolators.
name: Judicator

gametext: Deploy on table. While you occupy a Subjugated planet location, operatives are forfeit = 0, operatives do not add to Force drains and your Force drains may not be reduced. At any time, you may place Effect out of play to retrieve 1 Force. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "I will deal with them myself."
name: Leave Them To Me

gametext: Deploys -2 to any docking bay or launch bay. While he is at Death Star II: Docking Bay, you may shuttle for free between here and exterior sites related to system Death Star II orbits.
lore: Docking bay technician. Orphan. Offered post on new Death Star when he graduated third in class from the Imperial Academy at Carida.
name: Lieutenant Endicott

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Scythe 3, once per turn may subtract 1 from maneuver of one opponent's starfighter at same location for remainder of turn.
lore: Served in Anoat sector. Uses excellent maneuverability of TIE/ln to his advantage in combat.
name: Lieutenant Hebsly

gametext: Deploys -2 to \ul Executor\ul0, Death Star II or Endor. Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. While armed with a lightsaber, adds 2 to his defense value and 1 to each of his lightsaber weapon destiny draws. Immune to Uncontrollable Fury and attrition < 6.
lore: Forgiving administrator of Imperial policy. Emperor Palpatine's most trusted \b leader\b0. Believes converting Skywalker is key to the Alliance's downfall.
name: Lord Vader

gametext: Adds 3 to power of any TIE he pilots. Adds 2 to total weapon destiny of any TIE/ln he pilots.
lore: Commander of a TIE squadron assigned to defend the second Death Star during construction. Hand picked pilots to serve with him.
name: Major Mianda

gametext: Deploys -2 aboard Scimitar 1. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a bomber making a Bombing Run, prevents opponent's characters at same site from using landspeed.
lore: \b Leader\b0  of Scimitar Squadron, the elite bomber wing assigned to defend the Endor shield generator from any ground assault.
name: Major Rhymer

gametext: Adds 3 to power of any TIE he pilots. When piloting Saber 2, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Once per game, you may take Fighters Coming In into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Executive officer of 181st Imperial Fighter Wing. Older brother killed by Wedge Antilles at the Battle of Yavin.
name: Major Turr Phennir

gametext: Deploy on table. Your Force generation is +1 at each docking bay you occupy (or +2 if you control). Once per game, you may take one Carida, Wakeelmui, Gall, Kuat, or Rendili system or \ul Executor\ul0  into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The Imperial noose relies on swift troop dispatch from docking bays.
name: Mobilization Points

gametext: Adds 2 to power of any capital starship he pilots. Once during each of your turns, you may take one Death Star II sector or Superlaser Mark II into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Prevents opponent's spies from deploying to same Death Star II site.
lore: \b Leader\b0. Found discussions with Vader to be particularly motivating. Does not want to find out if the Emperor is more forgiving than Vader.
name: Moff Jerjerrod

dark_side_text: If you occupy with a Star Destroyer, opponent's Star Cruisers are deploy +2 (and may not deploy here).
gametext: Force drain -1 here. If you occupy with a Star Cruiser, opponent's Star Destroyers deploy +2 here.   If you occupy with a Star Destroyer, opponent's Star Cruisers are deploy +2 (and may not deploy here).
light_side_text: Force drain -1 here. If you occupy with a Star Cruiser, opponent's Star Destroyers deploy +2 here.
name: Mon Calamari

gametext: Deploys only on Coruscant or to Emperor's site (or related site). When armed with a Force pike, adds one battle destiny. Your troopers and Royal Guards may 'react' to here for free. Adds 1 to defense value of other Royal Guards at same and related sites.
lore: Royal Guard \b leader\b0. Remembers nothing of his past other than serving his Emperor. Early instructor of Kir Kanos and Carnor Jax.
name: Myn Kyneugh

gametext: May deploy with a pilot as a 'react' to any asteroid sector or cloud sector. May add one pilot. OS-72-10 deploys -2 aboard.
lore: Recalled to defend second Death Star during construction. Stationed aboard \ul Thunderflare\ul0.
name: Obsidian 10

gametext: May deploy -2 with a pilot as a 'react' to same location as any \ul Imperial\ul0 -class Star Destroyer. May add 1 pilot. Any starship cannon may deploy aboard. Immune to attrition < 4 when Jendon piloting.
lore: Designed to emulate Rebel starfighter advantages. Production began shortly before the Battle of Endor. Armed with laser cannons, ion cannons and missle launchers.
name: Onyx 1

gametext: Deploys for free to any mobile system. May deploy with a pilot as a 'react.' May add 1 pilot. Any starship cannon may deploy aboard. Immune to attrition < 4 when Yorr piloting.
lore: Part of limited production run of TIE defenders. Testing of the prototype defender indicated the need for a more powerful hyperdrive, which was added for this production model.
name: Onyx 2

gametext: USED: Place one card from hand on top of Force Pile. STARTING: If Endor system on table, take Death Star II system, Jerjerrod and any Effect into hand from Reserve Deck. When you draw your starting hand, draw only six more cards. Place Interrupt in Lost Pile.
lore: "We shall double our efforts."
name: Operational As Planned

gametext: Deploy on Emperor. While at a battleground planet site you control, at each related site where an Imperial is present, your Force drains are +1.
lore: Though reluctant to leave Coruscant, Emperor Palpatine occasionally finds it necessary to personally put lagging Imperial operations back on schedule.
name: Overseeing It Personally

gametext: USED: Add 1 to your battle destiny just drawn. STARTING: Deploy up to three Effects if each of them deploys for free, is always immune to Alter and has "deploy on table" (or "deploy on your side of table") in its game text. Place Interrupt in Lost Pile.
lore: Since the debacle at Yavin, the Emperor places a premium on the security of his costly war machine.
name: Prepared Defenses

gametext: If Emperor on Death Star II, take Vader into hand from a location you control (cards on him go to owner's hand). OR During your control phase, if Vader escorting Luke or Leia at a site you control, relocate Vader (with captive) to Death Star II: Docking Bay. (Immune to Sense.)
lore: "I sense you wish to continue your search for young Skywalker."
name: Rise, My Friend

gametext: Deploy on table. Each of your non-unique troopers on Endor or Death Star II is forfeit +1. When opponent just used a weapon to target your character aboard a piloted vehicle, that character may use that vehicle's defense value.
lore: When away from the Imperial Palace on Coruscant, the Emperor is protected by legions of troops. Typically this force includes soldiers trained to fight in the local environment.
name: Royal Escort

gametext: Deploys only on Coruscant or to Emperor's site (or related site). When armed with a Force pike and defending a battle, adds one battle destiny. Emperor may not be targeted by weapons unless all Royal Guards present with Emperor are 'hit'.
lore: Member of Emperor's Royal Guard. Completely subservient. Royal Guards must fight one of their own to the death in order to complete their training.
name: Royal Guard

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any TIE (for free if a TIE/ln). May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw Destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value.
lore: TIE cannon mass produced at Wakeelmui system. Compatible with multiple TIE models for ease of deployment throughout the fleet.
name: SFS L-s7.2 TIE Cannon

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Fel deploys -1 aboard. When firing SFS L-s9.3 Laser Cannons, may use 1 Force to make X = 3. Immune to attrition < 5 when Fel piloting.
lore: TIE interceptor serial number 000004. Assigned to Baron Soontir Fel of the fighting 181st. Bears the Saber Squadron bloodstripe, representing a minimum of 10 kills.
name: Saber 1

gametext: May add 1 pilot. When Phennir piloting, immune to attrition < 4 and adds 1 to forfeit of each other Saber Squadron pilot in same battle.
lore: TIE interceptor flown by Major Phennir. Assigned to protect \ul Avenger\ul0  at the Battle of Endor. Responsible for the logistics of Saber Squadron.
name: Saber 2

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Cannons are deploy -2 aboard. Immune to attrition < 3 when DS-181-3 piloting.
lore: TIE interceptor assigned to fly on the wing of Baron Fel. Often ordered to remain at a distance from Fel to give the Baron maneuvering room during combat.
name: Saber 3

gametext: May deploy with a pilot as a 'react' to a battle initiated where you have a TIE (for free if TIE is in Saber Squadron). May add 1 pilot. Immune to attrition < 4 when DS-181-4 piloting.
lore: TIE interceptor often assigned to fly in a reserve position during battle. The bloodstripe of the 181st denotes the 10 kills scored by DS-181-4.
name: Saber 4

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Power +3 during a Bombing Run battle. When proton bombs aboard 'collapse' a site, opponent loses 1 Force for each Rebel just lost.
lore: Scimitar bombing group TIE bomber. Equipped with advanced targeting system to increase damage during planetary bombardment.
name: Scimitar 1

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Power +3 during a Bombing Run battle. Once per game, you may deploy one Proton Bombs from Reserve Deck on this starfighter; reshuffle.
lore: TIE bomber repaired after being struck by an asteroid in the Anoat system. Stationed aboard second Death Star battle station.
name: Scimitar 2

gametext: Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Power +3 during a Bombing Run battle. Cumulatively adds 1 to total weapon destiny of your other TIE/SA present firing Concussion Missiles.
lore: Bombers typically assigned to attack secondary targets and provide cover during bombing runs. Targeting systems calibrated to track fast-moving Rebel starfighters.
name: Scimitar Squadron TIE

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Once during each of your move phases, may fire one starship weapon aboard ('hit' targets are lost) and/or make an additional move. Immune to attrition < 4 when Mianda piloting.
lore: TIE fighter garrisoned aboard second Death Star. Part of Scythe Squadron, a TIE group with upgraded SFS P-w702 maneuvering jets to increase performance in tight quarters.
name: Scythe 1

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Hebsly deploys -2 aboard. Once during each of your move phases, may fire one starship weapon aboard ('hit' targets are lost). Immune to attrition < 4 when Hebsly piloting.
lore: Heavily modified TIE/ln. Cannons upgraded to destroy small asteroids while serving in Anoat system. P-w702 maneuvering jets added by Death Star technicians.
name: Scythe 3

gametext: Deploy -2 to Death Star II or Endor. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2 and adds 1 to power and maneuver.
lore: Scythe Squadron TIE fighters are modified TIE/lns assigned to defend the second Death Star during construction. Their pilots fly frequent training missions within the Death Star.
name: Scythe Squadron TIE

gametext: Deploys -3 to Emperor's site. When with Emperor, adds one battle destiny. Once per turn, you may use 1 Force to peek at top card of opponent's Reserve Deck; may place that card on bottom of that Reserve Deck. Immune to attrition < 4.
lore: Imperial council member. Senior political advisor to Emperor Palpatine. Never speaks. Like his master, shows remarkable patience and wisdom.
name: Sim Aloo

gametext: Deploy on table. For opponent to move a starship from same location as your Star Destroyer requires +2 Force. Also, when opponent has just retrieved Force using an Interrupt or Utinni Effect card, that card is placed out of play. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The high command of the Emperor's fleet is selected as much for loyalty and obedience as for martial skills. A wise admiral knows better than to question Palpatine.
name: Something Special Planned For Them

dark_side_text: If you control when Haven is canceled, opponent loses 8 Force.
gametext: Immune to Revolution.   If you control when Haven is canceled, opponent loses 8 Force.
name: Sullust

gametext: Deploy on Death Star II system. May fire only when That Thing's Operational on table. May target a capital starship at Death Star II (or at the system Death Star II orbits) for free. Draw three destiny. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: The redesign of the Death Star called for improved defenses against Rebel starships. The superlaser redesign, while not able to target snub fighters, can devastate capital starships.
name: Superlaser Mark II

gametext: Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Power +1 when present with an X-wing. During each battle, may fire one starship weapon aboard twice.
lore: Advanced TIE design. Assigned to elite squadrons, such as the 181st. Developed with enhanced weapons and maneuverability to defeat the Incom X-wing design.
name: TIE Interceptor

gametext: Deploy on Reactor Core. Death Star II may move (hyperspeed = 3). While Death Star II orbits a system you occupy (except Endor), once during each of your control phases, opponent loses X Force, where X = 2 plus number of related battleground sites you occupy. Once during each of opponent's control phases, opponent's piloted starfighter here may attempt to "blow away" Death Star II. Draw destiny. Add 3 if armed with torpedoes or missiles. Add pilot's ability. If total destiny > 8, starships here may attempt to 'escape' and Death Star II is "blown away" (lose double Force).
name: That Thing's Operational

gametext: Deploys -2 to Endor, Death Star II or same location as Thrawn. May deploy as a 'react.' Permanent pilots provide total ability of 3. Power +3 at Endor or when Emperor is at same or related location.
lore: Top outer rim pilots hand picked by Admiral Thrawn. Sent to protect the Emperor during his inspection of the second Death Star.
name: The Emperor's Shield

gametext: Deploys -2 to Coruscant or Death Star II. May deploy as a 'react.' Permanent pilots provide total ability of 3. Power +3 at Coruscant or when Emperor is at same or related location.
lore: Elite pilots sworn to defend the Emperor to the death. Assigned older TIEs due to their years of experience with them. Stationed at Coruscant but always travel with the Emperor.
name: The Emperor's Sword

gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles, and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Turbolaser batteries deploy and fire free aboard.
lore: Overpowered Star Destroyer. Energy is transferred from hyperdrive to weapons. Patrol duties in the Core Worlds make it a common first assignment for junior officers.
name: Thunderflare

gametext: May deploy even without presence or Force icons (except to Rendezvous Point). May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1.
lore: Outfitted to chart unknown expanses of Outer Rim. Staff includes galactic cartography contingent. Considered a joke assignment by most lower-ranked Naval officers.
name: Visage

gametext: Each pilot deploys -1 (or -2 if an admiral) aboard a capital starship. Each capital starship with a pilot character aboard is immune to attrition < 4 (or adds 2 to immunity if starship already has immunity). During each of your control phases, opponent loses 1 Force for each battleground site your general or commander controls that is related to a system you occupy.
name: We're In Attack Position Now

gametext: Deploy on table. Opponent's Jedi are defense value -1. Never Tell Me The Odds is canceled. You may place Effect in Lost Pile to take one [Endor] or [Death Star II] Effect that deploys for free into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "Give yourself to the dark side. It is the only way you can save your friends."
name: You Cannot Hide Forever

gametext: If opponent's character present with Emperor was just lost, lose 1 Force to place that character out of play. OR Release frozen Luke at your Throne Room (Luke may not be battled unitl end of your next turn). OR Cancel NOOOOOOOOOOOO!
lore: "Now, young Skywalker . . . you will die."
name: Young Fool

gametext: Deploy on Bring Him Before Me. When Vader is present at a battleground site, at start of your turn opponent loses 3 Force unless Luke is captured, out of play or present at a battleground site. Also, Luke is immune to Responsibility of Command. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Luke's destiny lies with his father, Darth Vader. To become a Jedi Knight, Luke must accept this.
name: Your Destiny
